text_blocks.text:
By the end of this chapter, the reader should be able to:
* Identify key institutions that can champion CSA and its implementation using existing policy instruments that recognise CSA as a technology for improving food security;
* Identify all existing entry points for CSA implementation and establish the capacity needs to improve the design and implementation of the programmes;
* Identify and list institutional arrangements that can be established in the implementation of CSA; and
* Recommend policy statements for input into the national CSA legal/policy framework.
